review_blob: A perfect porter with a very deep body. Chocolate tone are combined with a caramel taste. Complex to describe but it fits. It is balanced.

Nice foam head after pooring the beer. The foam is stable. Very smooth RIS. It tastes like 6% but it is actually 8,5% vol. alc. Dangerous easy to drink. Light chocolate and coffee tones to begin with, followed by a strong "Laurier drop" aftertaste.
